<br>
I think most would consider EQ to be kinda the middle to the end of 1st gen MMORPG.  Maybe AC was the last 1st gen one.<br>
<br>
Let's put AO &amp; DAoC into the second gen.<br>
<br>
Verant with SoL has moved EQ from 1st gen to a leader in the 2nd gen.<br>
<br>
OK to be honest, considering the problems it didnt work out well but I think that is what they were trying.  And they kinda did it.  Or will when they get some problems worked out.<br>
<br>
People may look back and say SoL is where EQ &quot;jumped the shark&quot;.  Maybe even call it the biggest blunder ever.  However I think what they tried and to some extant have succeeded is somewhat remarkable.  The transformation of the game from one generation to another is an extremely bold step.<br>
<br>
The game could have survived with the same engine for at least 2 years (IMO).  Maybe they would have had to consolidate servers because of shrinking user base etc., but I would bet it would have still been alive.<br>
<br>
Verant tried to make it so EQ was still &quot;modern&quot; in the 2 year time frame.  The ironic part is it may end up shortening EQ life instead of prolonging it.  But I at least give em credit for attempting something extremely daring.<br>
<br>
